<_X_chapter sid="EZR 10">
<verse sid="EZR 10:1"/>And as Esdras prayed and as he declared, weeping and praying before the house of God, a very great assembly-- men and women and young men-- gathered to him from Israel, because the people wept and lifted up while weeping.<verse eid="EZR 10:1"/>

<verse sid="EZR 10:2"/>And Sechenias son of Ieiel, of Elam's sons, answered and said to Esdras, "We were faithless with our God and set up<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">10:2</char><char closed="false" style="ft">'set up':  I.e. 'married'</char></note> foreign women from the peoples of the land, and now there is endurance for Israel in this.<verse eid="EZR 10:2"/>

<verse sid="EZR 10:3"/>And now let us make a covenant with our God to cast out all the women and the issue from them, however you want. Arise, and scare them with the commandments of our God, and let it be done according to the law.<verse eid="EZR 10:3"/>

<verse sid="EZR 10:4"/>Arise! The word is upon you, and we are with you; be strong, and act."<verse eid="EZR 10:4"/>

<verse sid="EZR 10:5"/>And Esdras arose and made the rulers, the priests and Leuites and all Israel swear to act according to this word. And they swore.<verse eid="EZR 10:5"/>

<verse sid="EZR 10:6"/>And Esdras arose from before the house of God and went to the treasure chamber of Ioanan son of Elisoub, and he went there. He did not eat bread and did not drink water, because he was mourning over the faithlessness of the exile.<verse eid="EZR 10:6"/>

<verse sid="EZR 10:7"/>And they presented an utterance<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">10:7</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Or 'proclamation'</char></note> in Iouda and in Ierousalem to all sons of the exile that they should assemble in Ierousalem:<verse eid="EZR 10:7"/>

<verse sid="EZR 10:8"/>"Anyone who does not come within three days, as the council of the rulers and the elders demands<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">10:8</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Lacking in Greek</char></note>-- all his property will be anathematized, and he himself banned from the assembly of the exile."<verse eid="EZR 10:8"/>

<verse sid="EZR 10:9"/>And all the men of Iouda and Beniamin assembled to Ierousalem within the three days; this was the ninth month. On the twentieth of the month, all the people sat in the open square of the house of God, from their tumult about<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">10:9</char><char closed="false" style="ft">'tumult about':  Or 'clamor after'</char></note> the word and because of the winter.<verse eid="EZR 10:9"/>

<verse sid="EZR 10:10"/>And Esdras the priest arose and said to them, "You have been faithless and set up<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">10:10</char><char closed="false" style="ft">'set up':  I.e. 'married'</char></note> foreign women, increasing the error of Israel.<verse eid="EZR 10:10"/>

<verse sid="EZR 10:11"/>And now give praise to the Lord God of our fathers, and do what is pleasing before him, and separate from the peoples of the land and from the foreign women."<verse eid="EZR 10:11"/>

<verse sid="EZR 10:12"/>And all the assembly answered with a loud voice and said, "This word of yours is a big thing for us to do.<verse eid="EZR 10:12"/>

<verse sid="EZR 10:13"/>But the people are many, and it is the winter season, and there is no ability to stand outside, and the task is not for one day and not for two, because we have multiplied in doing wrong in this matter.<verse eid="EZR 10:13"/>

<verse sid="EZR 10:14"/>Let now our rulers stand fast for the whole assembly and for all those in our cities. As for him who has set up<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">10:14</char><char closed="false" style="ft">'set up':  I.e. 'married'</char></note> foreign women-- let them come at appropriate times as instructed, and with them the elders of city by city and judges, in order to turn away from us the anger of the wrath of our God concerning this matter."<verse eid="EZR 10:14"/>

<verse sid="EZR 10:15"/>Only Ionathan son of Asael and Iazias son of Thekoue are with me in this, and Mesoulam and Sabbathai the Leuite supporting them.<verse eid="EZR 10:15"/>

<verse sid="EZR 10:16"/>And sons of the exile did so. And Esdras the priest and men ruling the paternal houses were set apart<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">10:16</char><char closed="false" style="ft">'were set apart':  Or 'given express orders'</char></note>, and all by name, because on the first day of the tenth month they turned to investigate the matter.<verse eid="EZR 10:16"/>

<verse sid="EZR 10:17"/>And they finished with all the men who had set up<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">10:17</char><char closed="false" style="ft">'set up':  I.e. 'married'</char></note> foreign women by the first day of the first month.<verse eid="EZR 10:17"/>

<verse sid="EZR 10:18"/>And there were found some sons of the priests who had set up<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">10:18</char><char closed="false" style="ft">'set up':  I.e. 'married'</char></note> foreign women: some sons of Iesous son of Iosedek and his brothers: Maaseia and Eliezer and Iarib and Gadalia.<verse eid="EZR 10:18"/>

<verse sid="EZR 10:19"/>And they gave their hand<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">10:19</char><char closed="false" style="ft">'gave their hand':  I.e. 'pledged'</char></note> to put away their wives and errors-- a ram of the flock for their error.<verse eid="EZR 10:19"/>

<verse sid="EZR 10:20"/>And of Emmer's sons: Hanania and Zabdia.<verse eid="EZR 10:20"/>

<verse sid="EZR 10:21"/>And of Heram's sons: Masias and Elia and Samaia and Ieiel and Ozia.<verse eid="EZR 10:21"/>

<verse sid="EZR 10:22"/>And of Phasour's sons: Elioenai, Maasia and Ismael and Nathanael and Iozabad and Elasa.<verse eid="EZR 10:22"/>

<verse sid="EZR 10:23"/>And of the Leuites: Iozabad and Samou and Kolia (that is, Kolitas) and Phetheia and Ioudas and Eliezer.<verse eid="EZR 10:23"/>

<verse sid="EZR 10:24"/>And of the singers: Elisab. And of the gatekeepers: Solmen and Telmen and Odoue.<verse eid="EZR 10:24"/>

<verse sid="EZR 10:25"/>And of Israel: of Phoros' sons: Ramia and Iazia and Melchia and Meamin and Eleazar and Hasabia and Banaia.<verse eid="EZR 10:25"/>

<verse sid="EZR 10:26"/>And of Elam's sons: Maththania and Zacharia and Iaiel and Abdia and Ieri-moth and Elia.<verse eid="EZR 10:26"/>

<verse sid="EZR 10:27"/>And of Zaththoua's sons: Elioenai, Elisoub, Maththanai and Iarmoth and Zabad and Oziza.<verse eid="EZR 10:27"/>

<verse sid="EZR 10:28"/>And of Babi's sons: Ioanan, Hanania and Zabou, Othali.<verse eid="EZR 10:28"/>

<verse sid="EZR 10:29"/>And of Bani's sons: Mesoulam, Malouch, Adaias, Iasoub and Saal and Re-moth.<verse eid="EZR 10:29"/>

<verse sid="EZR 10:30"/>And of Phaathmoab's sons: Edne and Chalel and Banaia, Maasea, Maththania, Beselel and Banoui and Manasse.<verse eid="EZR 10:30"/>

<verse sid="EZR 10:31"/>And of Heram's sons: Eliezer, Ieseia, Melchia, Samaias, Semeon,<verse eid="EZR 10:31"/>

<verse sid="EZR 10:32"/>Beniamin, Malouch, Samaria.<verse eid="EZR 10:32"/>

<verse sid="EZR 10:33"/>And of Hasem's sons: Maththanai, Maththatha, Zabad, Eliphalet, Ieremi, Manasse and Semei.<verse eid="EZR 10:33"/>

<verse sid="EZR 10:34"/>And of Bani's sons: Mood-ia, Amram and Ouel,<verse eid="EZR 10:34"/>

<verse sid="EZR 10:35"/>Banaia, Badaia, Chelia,<verse eid="EZR 10:35"/>

<verse sid="EZR 10:36"/>Ououania, Marimoth, Eliasib,<verse eid="EZR 10:36"/>

<verse sid="EZR 10:37"/>Maththania, Maththanai, and so did<verse eid="EZR 10:37"/>

<verse sid="EZR 10:38"/>Banoui's sons and Semei's sons<verse eid="EZR 10:38"/>

<verse sid="EZR 10:39"/>and Selemia and Nathan and Adaias,<verse eid="EZR 10:39"/>

<verse sid="EZR 10:40"/>Machnadaabou, Sesei, Arou,<verse eid="EZR 10:40"/>

<verse sid="EZR 10:41"/>Ezriel and Selemia and Samarias,<verse eid="EZR 10:41"/>

<verse sid="EZR 10:42"/>Selloum, Amarias, Ioseph.<verse eid="EZR 10:42"/>

<verse sid="EZR 10:43"/>And of Nabou's sons: Ieiel, Maththathias, Zabad, Zebinnas, Iadai and Ioel and Banaia.<verse eid="EZR 10:43"/>

<verse sid="EZR 10:44"/>All these had married foreign women, and they fathered sons by them.<verse eid="EZR 10:44"/>
</_X_chapter></_X_book></_X_usx>